issue.title: Occasional getting an assert when writing data.
issue.body:
I'm occasionally hitting the assert on line 463 of KDSoapServerSocket.cpp, not sure what is causing it.
After adding a little debug, i.e. changing the line to:

`Q_ASSERT_X(written == httpHeaders.size(), "writeXML", qPrintable(QStringLiteral("Only wrote %1 of %2 bytes").arg(written).arg(httpHeaders.size()))); // Please report a bug if you hit this.`

I'm getting:
ASSERT failure in writeXML: "Only wrote -1 of 64 bytes", file...

comment.body: Took nearly two months for this to pop up again, but yes I can confirm that this assert occured because the socket was closed.

pull_request.title: Fix compiler error C1061 when using more than 122 functions
pull_request.body:
If the WSDL file contains more than 122 functions, the code generated by kdwsdl2cpp throws compiler error C1061 (MSVC). This is caused by the huge if statement in processRequest().

Fixed by replacing else if with if in processRequest().
